<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5268] Service not unregistered while bundle is starting</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5268</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This bug has been reported by Bram from the felix users mailing list: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mail-archive.com/users%40felix.apache.org/msg17269.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.mail-archive.com/users%40felix.apache.org/msg17269.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-&amp;gt; When a bundle is starting, and if a service providing component is added from the Activator, then if the component is losing a required service dependency or if the component is intentionally removed from the activator, then the DM component is stopped, but any services provided by the component are not unregistered from the service registry.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
